## Output Type: BenchmarkResult

This is the primary output struct consumed by bd-5fj3 (report generator).
It aggregates all per-run metrics into a single serializable record per model.

```rust
use crate::models::ModelCategory;
use crate::benchmark::metrics::{SpeedMetrics, QualityMetrics};

/// Complete benchmark result for one model, consumed by report generator (bd-5fj3)
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct BenchmarkResult {
    pub model_name: String,
    pub category: ModelCategory,  // From bd-2crr: StaticEmbedder or TransformerEmbedder
    pub eligible: bool,           // release_date >= 2025-11-01 (from candidates list)
    pub release_date: Option<String>,

    // Quality metrics (from corpus evaluation)
    pub quality: QualityMetrics,

    // Speed metrics (from benchmark phases)
    pub speed: SpeedMetrics,

    // Reliability metrics
    pub total_requests: usize,
    pub errors: usize,
    pub oom_count: usize,
    pub panics: usize,

    // Resource usage
    pub peak_rss_mb: f64,
    pub steady_rss_mb: f64,
    pub model_file_size_mb: f64,
    pub peak_threads: usize,

    // MRL analysis (if model supports_mrl)
    pub mrl_dims_tested: Vec<usize>,
    pub mrl_quality_at_dims: Vec<(usize, f64)>,  // (dims, ndcg@10)

    // Reranker-specific (only for reranker benchmarks)
    pub reranker_lift: Option<f64>,  // % lift in NDCG@10 vs no-rerank
}

impl BenchmarkResult {
    /// Error rate as fraction (0.0-1.0)
    pub fn error_rate(&self) -> f64 {
        if self.total_requests == 0 { return 0.0; }
        self.errors as f64 / self.total_requests as f64
    }

    /// Is this result reliable enough for winner selection?
    pub fn is_reliable(&self) -> bool {
        self.error_rate() < 0.01 && self.oom_count == 0 && self.panics == 0
    }
}
```

## Implementation
Uses the Embedder and Reranker traits from bd-2crr (ModelRegistry) to load models.
No redundant trait - the benchmark runner is a consumer of the trait interfaces.

```rust
use crate::models::{Embedder, Reranker, ModelRegistry, ModelCategory};

struct BenchmarkRun {
    model: Box<dyn Embedder>,
    corpus: Corpus,
    config: BenchmarkConfig,
    collector: MetricCollector, // from bd-164
}

impl BenchmarkRun {
    /// Execute full benchmark and produce BenchmarkResult
    pub fn execute(&mut self) -> Result<BenchmarkResult> {
        // 1. Cold start phase
        let cold_start = self.measure_cold_start()?;

        // 2. Warmup phase (discard metrics)
        for _ in 0..self.config.warmup_iterations {
            self.model.embed_batch(&self.corpus.sample_batch())?;
        }

        // 3. Measurement phase
        let mut latencies = Vec::with_capacity(self.config.measure_iterations);
        let mut errors = 0usize;
        let mut oom_count = 0usize;

        for _ in 0..self.config.measure_iterations {
            let batch = self.corpus.sample_batch();
            let start = Instant::now();
            match self.model.embed_batch(&batch) {
                Ok(_) => latencies.push(start.elapsed()),
                Err(e) if is_oom(&e) => { oom_count += 1; errors += 1; }
                Err(_) => { errors += 1; }
            }
        }

        // 4. Quality evaluation (using ground truth from corpus)
        let quality = self.evaluate_quality()?;

        // 5. MRL sweep (if supported)
        let (mrl_dims, mrl_quality) = if self.model.supports_mrl() {
            self.mrl_sweep(&[64, 128, 256, 512, 768, 1024])?
        } else {
            (vec![], vec![])
        };

        // 6. Resource measurement
        let rss = get_process_rss_mb();

        Ok(BenchmarkResult {
            model_name: self.model.model_name().to_string(),
            category: self.model.category(),  // From Embedder trait
            eligible: self.config.candidates.is_eligible(&self.model.model_name()),
            release_date: self.config.candidates.release_date(&self.model.model_name()),
            quality,
            speed: SpeedMetrics {
                cold_start_ms: cold_start.as_secs_f64() * 1000.0,
                warm_latency_p50_ms: percentile(&latencies, 0.50),
                warm_latency_p95_ms: percentile(&latencies, 0.95),
                warm_latency_p99_ms: percentile(&latencies, 0.99),
                throughput_docs_per_sec: compute_throughput(&latencies, self.config.batch_size),
                time_to_first_result_ms: cold_start.as_secs_f64() * 1000.0 + latencies[0].as_secs_f64() * 1000.0,
            },
            total_requests: self.config.measure_iterations,
            errors,
            oom_count,
            panics: 0,
            peak_rss_mb: rss,
            steady_rss_mb: rss * 0.9,  // Approximation
            model_file_size_mb: self.model_file_size_mb(),
            peak_threads: rayon::current_num_threads(),
            mrl_dims_tested: mrl_dims,
            mrl_quality_at_dims: mrl_quality,
            reranker_lift: None,
        })
    }
}
```

### Benchmark phases
1. Cold start: model load + first embed (measures TTFR)
2. Warmup: 10 iterations (discard, allows JIT/cache warmup)
3. Measurement: 100 iterations with percentile tracking
4. Quality evaluation: using ground truth corpus from bd-cy0
5. MRL sweep: if model supports_mrl(), benchmark at multiple dims
6. Optional rerank phase: if --reranker specified
7. Report generation: JSON + Markdown + terminal summary

### Warmup Strategy
- Separate cold vs warm timings (critical for static vs transformer comparison)
- Capture TTFR (Time to First Result) as distinct metric
- Record CPU/core count and thread pool size
- Log whether ONNX runtime uses AVX2/AVX-512

## Output Formats
- JSON: machine-readable `Vec<BenchmarkResult>` with full metric breakdown
- Markdown: human-readable comparison table
- Terminal: colored summary with winner highlights
- JSONL trace: raw per-iteration latencies for offline analysis

